Signal Aggregation Engine (SIG)
Documentation Master Plan (Aligned to NS-GGP Canonical Template)
PurposeThis document defines the authoritative documentation master plan for SIG, strictly aligned to the existing NS-GGP document structure (000–014).
SIG is the signal intake, normalization, and trust-scoring engine for Northfield Solidarity. It collects raw signals from many sources and produces clean, provenance-aware, trust-scored signals for downstream engines. SIG does not generate insights (PIE), execute actions (DAT), or govern decisions (GGP).

SIG Documentation Index (Canonical)

NS-SIG-000 — CHARTER
Purpose: Define why SIG exists
Scope:
Mission of SIG
Why signal aggregation must be centralized
SIG’s role as the entry point for market intelligence
Explicit non-goals (insight synthesis, execution, governance)
Mirrors: NS-GGP-000

